---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Sa Re Ga Ma — Seven Swaras | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Master India's musical alphabet — the seven swaras that form the foundation of all music. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Sa Re Ga Ma — Seven Swaras</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-beginner capitalize">beginner</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 20 min · Lesson 3 of 8</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Sa Re Ga Ma — Seven Swaras</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Master India's musical alphabet — the seven swaras that form the foundation of all music.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Seven swaras: Sa Re Ga Ma Pa Dha Ni</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Sa and Pa are achala (fixed) — never altered</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Ascending (aroha): A S D F G H J K on keyboard</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Descending (avaroha): K J H G F D S A on keyboard</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Always sing swara names while playing them</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>The Seven Swaras</h2>
      <p>Indian classical music uses seven fundamental notes called swaras. Their full Sanskrit names are Shadja (Sa), Rishabh (Re), Gandhar (Ga), Madhyama (Ma), Pancham (Pa), Dhaivat (Dha), and Nishad (Ni). These correspond to Western notes C D E F G A B. After Ni the cycle repeats — the next note is Sa one octave higher.</p>

      <h2>Ascending Scale Practice</h2>
      <p>Play each swara clearly and hold it for one beat saying the name aloud: Sa... Re... Ga... Ma... Pa... Dha... Ni... Sa. On the web harmonium use keyboard keys A S D F G H J K. Repeat this ascending scale 10 times slowly before increasing speed. Focus on even timing and equal volume on each note.</p>

      <h2>Descending Scale Practice</h2>
      <p>Now reverse direction: Sa Ni Dha Pa Ma Ga Re Sa. Keys: K J H G F D S A. Many beginners find descending harder than ascending — this is completely normal. The descending scale trains different neural pathways and requires separate focused practice. Give descending equal time as ascending.</p>

      <h2>The Sa Pa Interval</h2>
      <p>Pa is the most harmonious note with Sa — the perfect fifth in Indian music. Play Sa (A) and Pa (G) together and listen to how naturally they blend. This Sa-Pa consonance is the foundation of the harmonium drone used in all classical accompaniment. Practice this interval until you can find Pa instantly.</p>

      <h2>Singing While Playing</h2>
      <p>The single most powerful practice habit is singing swara names while playing. Even if you are not a singer vocalize softly. This builds the crucial connection between what you hear what you say and what your fingers do. Musicians who develop this habit from the beginning progress noticeably faster than those who do not.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>